den VH Commodore|Holden VH Commodore SS]]\n| [[Marlboro Holden Dealer Team]]\n|-\n! 1984\n| [[1984 Australian Endurance Championship|Australian Endurance Championship]]\n|align=\"center\" | 5th\n| [[Holden VK Commodore]]\n| [[Marlboro Holden Dealer Team]]\n|-\n! 1985\n| [[1985 Australian Touring Car Championship|Australian Touring Car Championship]]\n|align=\"center\" | 38th\n| [[Holden VK Commodore]]\n| [[Mobil Holden Dealer Team]]\n|-\n!rowspan=2| 1986\n| [[1986 Australian Endurance Championship|Australian Endurance Championship]]\n|align=\"center\" | 24th\n|rowspan=2| [[Holden VK Commodore SS Group A]]\n|rowspan=2| [[Perkins Engineering|Enzed Team Perkins]]\n|-\n| [[South Pacific Touring Car Championship]]\n|align=\"center\" | 14th\n|-\n! 1987\n| [[1987 Australian Touring Car Championship|Australian Touring Car Championship]]\n|align=\"center\" | 5th\n| [[Holden VK Commodore SS Group A]]\n| [[Perkins Engineering|Enzed Team Perkins]]\n|-\n!rowspan=3| 1988\n| [[1988 Australian Touring Car Championship|Australian Touring Car Championship]]\n|align=\"center\" | 7th\n| [[Holden VL Commodore SS Group A]]\n| [[Perkins Engineering|Holden Special Vehicles]]\n|-\n| [[1988 Asia-Pacific Touring Car Championship|Asia-Pacific Touring Car Championship]]\n|align=\"center\" | 6th\n| [[Holden VL Commodore SS Group A]]\n| [[Perkins Engineering|Holden Special Vehicles]]\n|-\n| [[1988 World Sportscar Championship season|World Sports Prototype Championship]]\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"| 29th\n| [[Jaguar XJR-9]]\n| [[Tom Walkinshaw Racing|Silk Cut]] [[Jaguar Cars|Jaguar]]\n|-\n! 1989\n| [[1989 Australian Touring Car Championship|Australian Touring Car Championship]]\n|align=\"center\" | 17th\n| [[Holden VL Commodore SS Group A SV]]\n| [[Perkins Engineering]]\n|-\n!rowspan=2| 1990\n| [[1990 Australian Touring Car Championship|Australian Touring Car Championship]]\n|align=\"center\" | 11th\n|rowspan=2| [[Holden VL Commodore SS Group A SV]]\n|rowspan=2| [[Perkins Engineering]]\n|-\n| [